lead_paragraph: The Los Angeles Lakers began the game without four injured regulars, and lost a fifth in the second half. The Utah Jazz were merely without their coach and second-leading scorer.

headline.print_headline: Jazz Hold Off Lakers' Rally to Win Without Snyder, 107-101
